                "reference": "fc302_selection_guide.pdf"
            }
        ],
        "scope": "FC 302 only. FC 202 ignored as requested.",
        "notes": [
            "Typecode is a 39-character string.",
            "A/B/C documentation and D/E documentation use the same 39-position structure, but the A/B/C design guide splits product group and drive series differently than the D/E guide.",
            "Where the manuals differ in positional labeling, the JSON below normalizes to one rigid 39-position model and records the discrepancy in conflicts."
        ]
    },
    "typecode_structure": [
        {
            "segment_name": "product_group_series",
            "character_positions": "1-6",
            "raw_example": "FC-302",
            "notes": "Normalized rigid segment. D/E guide shows Product group 1-6 = FC-302. A/B/C guide splits this as Product group 1-3 and Drive series 4-6."
        },
        {
            "segment_name": "model_or_power_rating",
            "character_positions": "7-10",
            "notes": "For FC 302 this is the power/model code, for example PK75, N355."
        },
        {
            "segment_name": "phases_and_mains_voltage",
            "character_positions": "11-12",
            "notes": "In A/B/C guide character 11 is phase T and 11-12 together define T2/T4/T5/T6/T7. In practice parse as one combined 2-character segment."
